name: Q Ball
description: Deep Rose with Yellow anthers. Very large, peony form. Vigorous, upright, dense growth. E-L. (U.S. 2010 - Eleanor Grant, Dothan, AL).

name: Qingkou
description: See 'Empty Mouth'.

name: Quaintance
description: Soft Pink lightly striped Darker Pink. Medium, semidouble. (Sport of Japonica 'Herme'). (U.S. 1950 - McCaskill).

name: Quaker Lady
description: Salmon Pink. Large, semidouble. (Sport of Japonica 'Carter's Carnival'). (U.S. 1959 - Carter).

name: Que Sera Sera
description: Salmon Pink. Large to very large, variform; regular semidouble to semidouble with petaloids intermixed with stamens to anemone form. Vigorous, compact, upright growth. E-M. (U.S. 1982 - Nuccio's).

name: Queen Bee
description: Soft Pink. Very large, irregular semidouble. Vigorous, upright growth. M-L. (Reticulata seedling). (U.S. 1993 - Nuccio's).

name: Queen Bessie
description: White flushed Pink at center. Medium, semidouble with wavy petals. Vigorous, compact, upright growth. L. (U.S. 1935 - Overlook).

name: Queen Diana
description: Pink shading to Pale Pink in outer petals. Medium, formal double. Vigorous, spreading, open growth. E-L. (N.Z. 1985 - J. C. Lesnie, Wanukau).

name: Queen Juliana
description: See 'Southern Charm'.

name: Queen Of England
description: Cherry Red striped White on inner petals. Medium, formal double. (England 1851 - Fiedler).

name: Queen Of Hearts
description: Bright Dark Red with Purple shading on edges with Yellow anthers and Pink filaments. Large, semidouble. Average, upright, open growth. M-L. (Seedling of Japonica 'Ville de Nantes'). (U.S. 2019 - Pat Johnson, Cairo, GA).

name: Queen Of The Acres
description: White to Pale Pink with Pink to Red streaks. Medium, formal double. (Sport of Japonica 'Rose Queen'). (U.S. 1951 - Councilman).

name: Queen Of The South
description: Blush Pink. Medium, full peony form. Compact, upright growth. E. (U.S. 1954 - Shackelford).

name: Queen Of Tomorrow
description: Heavy textured, lightly crinkled, fluted, edged petals and thick, leathery foliage. Large to very large, semidouble. (Sport of Japonica "Tomorrow Variegated'). (U.S. 1971 - Charmwood Nsy., Milbrook, AL).

name: Queen Tut
description: White. Medium, peony form. Average, upright growth. M-L. (U.S. 1991 - J. Aldrich, Brooklet, GA).

name: Queen Victoria's Blush (South)
description: See 'Souv. de Bahuaud Litou.

name: Queen's Court
description: White. Large, semidouble with heavy petals. M. (U.S. 1973 - Haynie).

name: Queen's Escort
description: Rose Pink with Silver sheen around edge of petals. Medium, semidouble. Vigorous, compact, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1959 - Dr. A Mazyck, Dothan, AL).

name: Queenslander
description: Soft Silver Pink. Medium, rose form double opening from bud center.

name: Quintessence
description: White with Yellow anthers and White filaments. Miniature, single. Slow, spreading growth. E-M. Fragrant. (Lutchuensis hybrid). (N.Z. 1985 - J. C. Lesnie, Wanakau).
